{{Quote|The way I saw Juno at the very beginning in ''The Force Unleashed'' is that she was this girl who was brought up in a strict, regimented way: you go to school, you get good grades, and you live life in a certain way. She was focused, almost to a fault, extremely intelligent, and she rose through the Imperial ranks very quickly. During the course of ''The Force Unleashed'' the rug gets pulled out from under her. She's branded a traitor, she's lost her way to a degree, and for the first time in her life she's unsure of herself. Yet at the same time, this guy comes along and she begins to have genuine feelings &mdash;romantic feelings&mdash; for him; feelings she's never had for another human being.|Nathalie Cox|<ref name="Insider 121">{{InsiderCite|120|Juno and the Jedi}}</ref>}}
'''Nathalie Cox''' is an English actress and model.

An actress with British accent was needed to fill the role of [[Juno Eclipse/Legends|Juno Eclipse]], consistent with the speech of the [[Galactic Empire|Imperial]] characters of the [[original trilogy]]. The team travelled to London, where casting director [[Kate Saxson]] helped in selecting a number of candidates before choosing Cox.<ref>''[[The Art and Making of Star Wars: The Force Unleashed]]''</ref>

[[File:JunoEclipseHS-TFU.png|thumb|left|160px|Captain Juno Eclipse]]
She portrayed Juno in the [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed]]'' and its sequel, ''[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed II]]'' through motion capture and voice work. She was on ''The Force Unleashed'' panel along with her co-star [[Sam Witwer]] at [[Celebration IV]].

Before and after ''The Force Unleashed'', she starred in three films with people who have worked in the ''Star Wars'' universe. She appeared in ''Kingdom of Heaven'' along with Irish actor [[Liam Neeson]] ([[Qui-Gon Jinn]]). She next made a cameo appearance in [[Wikipedia:Jumper (film)|''Jumper'']] starring [[Hayden Christensen]] ([[Anakin Skywalker]] in [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|Episode II]] and [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|Episode III]]) and [[Samuel L. Jackson]] ([[Mace Windu]]). She later starred alongside Liam Neeson again, as well as [[Mads Mikkelsen]] ([[Galen Walton Erso|Galen Erso]]), in the film [[Wikipedia:Clash of the Titans (2010 film)|''Clash of the Titans'']].

